# VMware workstation 12
# Ubuntu 64
## Problem Statement
# When server shutdown/poweroff unexpected, then the lock file may be not removed properly.
# Then the vm server may have a boot error: Failed to lock the file, cannot open the disk ***.vmdk or one of the snapshot is depends on. 
# Module Disk power on fialed. Failed to start the virutal machine.

# Solution:
delete/backup the lock files of the virtual machine.
The lock files locate at the virtualmachines directory, together with the vmdk and vmsd 


## Reference
www.networknet.nl/apps/wp/archives/396/comment-page-1



